message.content:
```
[A-Za-z0-9]{3}\.usfm$
```
Explanation:
- `[A-Za-z0-9]` matches any character that is either an upper or lower case letter (`A-Za-z`) or a digit (`0-9`). This creates a character class that can match the three characters of our code.
- `{3}` specifies that we want to match exactly 3 characters from the previous character class.
- `\.usfm$` matches the literal dot followed by "usfm" and the end of the line (`$`) to ensure that this matches only at the end of the filename.
